<i> -(tires screech)</i>
<i> -BEATRICE: Samuel!</i>

00:18.244 --> 00:20.627
<i> -(car crashing)</i>
<i> -(Beatrice screaming)</i>

00:20.779 --> 00:23.063
<i> ATHENA:</i>
<i> Mama?</i>

00:30.180 --> 00:32.531
(slow, rhythmic beeping)

00:35.202 --> 00:36.851
ATHENA:
He's in a coma.

00:36.871 --> 00:38.853
PINO:
Medically induced.

00:39.765 --> 00:42.023
It was significant,
and we want to give the brain

00:42.117 --> 00:43.950
time to heal on its own.

00:44.103 --> 00:46.770
BOBBY:
How long will he be sedated?

00:46.863 --> 00:48.939
PINO:
At least 24 hours.

00:49.032 --> 00:53.277
Run more tests,
then see where we are tomorrow.

00:53.295 --> 00:54.869
And then we can take him home?

00:54.963 --> 00:57.781
PINO:
Mrs. Carter, your husband
suffered an ischemic stroke.

00:57.800 --> 01:00.634
It's not only serious,
but the prognosis is uncertain.

01:00.786 --> 01:02.561
Samuel's very strong.

01:02.788 --> 01:04.805
I have no doubt,
but we don't know how he will

01:04.957 --> 01:07.457
or will not respond
to the treatment.

01:07.551 --> 01:08.642
We have to be prepared.

01:08.794 --> 01:10.885
Do not t-take that tone
with me, young man.

01:10.905 --> 01:12.905
BOBBY:
I think what Dr. Pino is saying
is that right now we just need

01:13.132 --> 01:15.132
-to be patient, that's all.
-That's correct.

01:15.225 --> 01:17.058
I have to run these tests.
He won't even be in the room.

01:17.078 --> 01:20.496
