like he took a hit.

07:43.130 --> 07:46.414
Check him out.
Find out what he knows.

07:48.043 --> 07:50.635
<i>HEN: Hey, Chimney, the homeowner</i>
<i> says it's underneath the carpet</i>

07:50.862 --> 07:53.530
<i>-beneath the rollaway shoe rack.</i>
-I see it, copy that.

07:53.548 --> 07:56.366
All right, sir,
checking for concussions.

07:56.459 --> 07:59.519
-Sir, what year is it?
-It's the year
my marriage ended.

08:00.964 --> 08:03.023
(laughing)

08:05.544 --> 08:07.569
Anybody hear me?

08:08.822 --> 08:11.564
LAFD. Can you hear me?

08:11.717 --> 08:14.201
Gary? What's this?

08:15.570 --> 08:17.478
I got a hand!

08:17.498 --> 08:18.663
Take it easy, Gary.

08:18.815 --> 08:20.665
Just checking your vitals.

08:20.834 --> 08:22.483
<i> Hey, Cap, I found him.</i>

08:22.503 --> 08:25.078
<i> He's conscious,</i>
<i> but his pulse is really low.</i>

08:25.230 --> 08:26.838
He's in one piece,
but I'm gonna need a hand

08:26.990 --> 08:28.673
<i> -getting him out of here.</i>
-Buck?

08:28.825 --> 08:30.008
I'm on it, Cap.

08:30.159 --> 08:32.177
<i> CHIMNEY:</i>
<i> Hen, there's something else!</i>

08:32.328 --> 08:35.013
<i> Gary's got nails</i>
<i> in his shoulder.</i>

08:35.164 --> 08:37.682
Shrapnel? Against gophers?

08:37.834 --> 08:40.560
Yeah, the rodent had it coming.

08:45.100 --> 08:48.193
Oh, my God, Gary! Are you okay?

08:48.420 --> 08:50.695
-Are you okay?
-Step down.

08:55.869 --> 08:57.427
You knew.

08:57.445 --> 08:58.686
Didn't you?

08:58.780 --> 08:59.946
I suspected.

09:00.098 --> 09:03.959
I didn't know for sure
until she called 911.

09:04.711 --> 09:07.379
Eddie, zip-tie his hands.

09:07.606 --> 09:09.138
Wait. What?

09:09.140 --> 09:11.775
Ow, what? No.
What are you talking about?

09:11.868 --> 09:14.594
-Ow!
-Sir, you're under arrest.

09:15.538 --> 09:16.462
Dispatch?

09:16.615 --> 09:18.448
This is Captain 118.
We're gonna need

09:18.466 --> 09:19.966
a black-and-white
at our current location.

09:20.060 --> 09:21.876
Our backyard accident

09:21.895 --> 09:24.545
seems to be an attempted murder.
We've apprehended a suspect.

09:24.623 --> 09:26.472
How can you--?
How are you allowed to do this?

09:26.625 --> 09:30.460
All LAFD personnel are sworn
peace officers.

09:30.462 --> 09:32.312
It's been that way
for about 100 years?

09:32.464 --> 09:33.313
See?

09:33.465 --> 09:36.700
You've learned two things today.

09:56.579 --> 09:59.823
Mama, the car's
still in the house.

09:59.841 --> 10:02.659
Your father will deal
with it when he gets home.

10:02.752 --> 10:05.178
Mama, you do realize
that Daddy is not coming home

10:05.330 --> 10:07.497
-for a while.
-Don't be ridiculous.

10:07.590 --> 10:08.832
He'll be fine.

10:08.850 --> 10:10.183
I'll go get your room ready.

10:10.277 --> 10:11.835
Would you rather
we stay in a hotel?

10:11.928 --> 10:13.278
Maybe you should.

10:13.505 --> 10:17.173
-Mama!
-Well, nobody asked you
to invade my home.

10:17.266 --> 10:20.267
I haven't pulled
that trundle bed out in years.

10:20.287 --> 10:22.178
Maybe your big,
strong fireman can do it.

10:22.197 --> 10:24.197
-Mama, I swear...
-It-It's okay.

10:24.349 --> 10:26.374
It's okay. Beatrice,
we'll set ourselves up.

10:27.610 --> 10:30.353
I do not know
what is in her head.

10:30.446 --> 10:33.539
Well, her world did just
crash down around her.

10:34.283 --> 10:36.542
Well, this does look worse
than I thought.

10:36.695 --> 10:38.285
But I can get
the car out of there,

10:38.305 --> 10:40.305
board up the windows.
We will need to contact

10:40.532 --> 10:42.641
-a contractor...
-That we have.

10:42.792 --> 10:44.033
Old family friend.

10:44.127 --> 10:45.292
I think he's still
their handyman.

10:45.312 --> 10:48.313
You think you can get
this car out of here

10:48.464 --> 10:49.706
by yourself?

10:49.799 --> 10:51.691
Big, strong fireman.

10:56.731 --> 10:58.639
What are you reading, Buck?

10:58.659 --> 11:00.307
Oh, it's, uh, it's Bobby's.

11:01.144 --> 11:03.644
Oh, are you trying
to tell us something?

11:03.738 --> 11:05.571
Um, no, he just, he told me

11:05.666 --> 11:07.982
about this idea in AA.
I took it upon myself

11:08.001 --> 11:10.985
to, you know,
dig a little deeper.

11:11.062 --> 11:14.339
Hey, can...
can I ask you something?

11:15.342 --> 11:16.582
Sure.

11:16.735 --> 11:17.901
Are you at ease?

11:17.919 --> 11:20.679
Do I look
like I'm at ease, Buck?

11:20.830 --> 11:23.740
No, sorry, wrong question.
It's just in-in the book,

11:23.758 --> 11:26.000
it says that if I'm at ease,

11:26.094 --> 11:29.913
"all my fear will fall
away from me."

11:29.931 --> 11:32.807
Well, let me know
how that works out.

11:32.859 --> 11:35.360
Yes, sir,
I hear the sirens, too.

11:35.511 --> 11:37.678
You're welcome.

11:37.772 --> 11:40.273
What did we say about lurking,
Noah?

11:40.425 --> 11:42.275
Sorry.

11:42.427 --> 11:44.277
I just wanted to thank you.

11:44.429 --> 11:47.521
For saving me, you know,
when I crashed and burned.

11:47.615 --> 11:50.208
You didn't do
either of those things.

11:50.359 --> 11:52.377
Today you learned
how the element of surprise

11:52.528 --> 11:55.605
-can refocus
a caller's attention.
-And if that doesn't work?

11:55.698 --> 11:57.123
Try singing to them.

11:57.292 --> 12:00.719
There was this guy who went off
Mulholland into the ravine.

12:00.795 --> 12:02.795
