Be still my heart.

14:47.795 --> 14:50.296
♪<i> Tell me if you hear me</i> ♪

14:50.448 --> 14:52.131
♪<i> Turn the music up...</i> ♪

14:52.283 --> 14:54.225
What medication
is taken to prevent

14:54.452 --> 14:55.952
-kidney transplant rejection?
-Cyclosporine.

14:55.970 --> 14:58.545
And what side effect is often
experienced with cyclosporine?

14:58.640 --> 15:00.289
Gingival hyperplasia

15:00.308 --> 15:03.960
can be caused by cyclosporine A.
The enlargement can be made

15:03.978 --> 15:05.844
worse by the accumulation
of plaque. Sir,

15:05.906 --> 15:07.071
when's the last time

15:07.223 --> 15:08.740
-you saw your dentist?
-CHIMNEY: I think he has

15:08.891 --> 15:11.743
-more pressing issues, Hen.
-HEN: Right, but he should

15:11.894 --> 15:12.985
-see a dentist.
-CHIMNEY: He should also

15:13.138 --> 15:14.303
stop running with scissors.

15:14.322 --> 15:15.914
Have you learned
nothing in school?

15:16.065 --> 15:17.081
-♪<i> Say it</i> ♪
-♪<i> Yeah, yeah</i> ♪

15:17.233 --> 15:18.732
♪<i> Well, I'm ready for ya</i> ♪

15:18.752 --> 15:19.751
♪<i> Come let me show ya</i> ♪

15:19.827 --> 15:20.977
♪<i> You want to groove</i> ♪

15:21.070 --> 15:22.495
♪<i> I'm-a show you how to move</i> ♪

15:22.647 --> 15:24.738
♪<i> Come, Mr. DJ,</i>
<i> song pon de replay</i> ♪

15:24.758 --> 15:26.332
♪<i> Come, Mr. DJ, won't you turn</i> ♪

15:26.484 --> 15:28.501
♪<i> The music up? All the gyal</i>
<i> pon the dance floor...</i> ♪

15:28.653 --> 15:29.910
How you like me now?

15:30.004 --> 15:32.263
♪<i> Mr. DJ, won't you turn</i>
<i> the music up?</i> ♪

15:38.271 --> 15:40.647
Yeah!

15:50.525 --> 15:52.241
♪ ♪

15:54.179 --> 15:56.345
T.A.:
All right, class, you have

15:56.364 --> 15:58.331
55 minutes to complete the test.

16:25.710 --> 16:28.111
♪ ♪

16:32.050 --> 16:35.118
(clock ticking)

17:00.912 --> 17:02.311
(sighs)

17:24.786 --> 17:27.694
(horn honking)

17:27.789 --> 17:29.438
(tires screech)

17:29.457 --> 17:31.090
(grunts)

17:33.553 --> 17:36.387
(panting)

17:43.396 --> 17:44.562
KAREN:
Hey.

17:44.713 --> 17:46.122
You're up early.

17:46.124 --> 17:48.357
-Yeah...
-I didn't hear you
come to bed last night.

17:49.794 --> 17:50.976
W... Did you

17:51.129 --> 17:52.695
come to bed last night?

17:55.967 --> 17:57.483
(sighs)

17:57.635 --> 18:00.060
I was pretty wired
when I got home.

18:00.154 --> 18:02.805
Needed a little time
to decompress.

18:02.807 --> 18:04.916
-You also need to sleep.
-Yeah.

18:05.067 --> 18:07.568
What time is it?
I probably could get

18:07.662 --> 18:08.978
a couple of hours before...

18:08.996 --> 18:11.480
(phone alarm rings)

18:11.574 --> 18:13.633
I die.

18:14.502 --> 18:15.835
You're going in early?

18:15.929 --> 18:18.487
Yeah, I'm behind on my 902m's.

18:18.506 --> 18:19.764
You should not
have talked yourself

18:19.991 --> 18:20.932
into the captain's chair.

18:21.125 --> 18:23.843
It's only for a few more days.

18:23.995 --> 18:26.829
Bobby will be back soon.

18:26.848 --> 18:28.848
Okay.

18:29.000 --> 18:31.692
Just... try to get
some sleep before then.

18:32.761 --> 18:34.529
I promise.

18:50.872 --> 18:52.964
(chuckles) Athena Carter.

18:53.115 --> 18:56.375
Junior.
(laughs) You are not

18:56.527 --> 18:58.544
the Franklin
that I was expecting.

18:58.696 --> 19:00.863
Pop's mostly retired
at this point,

19:00.882 --> 19:02.323
but you're in good hands.

19:02.325 --> 19:03.641
Man taught me everything I know.

19:03.792 --> 19:07.036
-(laughs)
-It's all right.
It's good to see you.

19:07.129 --> 19:08.980
Oh, my g--
Oh, this is my husband,

19:09.131 --> 19:11.107
-Bobby Nash.
-Nice to meet you.

19:11.967 --> 19:13.392
Been too long, Athena.

19:13.544 --> 19:15.636
When you left for California,
all of us were a little sad.

19:15.655 --> 19:17.488
(laughs) You were sad

19:17.640 --> 19:19.715
because you lost
your favorite target.

19:19.808 --> 19:21.308
This boy chased me

19:21.327 --> 19:22.994
-all through the orange groves.
-(laughs)

19:23.221 --> 19:24.236
(both laugh)

19:24.330 --> 19:25.812
Listen, I did what I could,
but the place

19:25.907 --> 19:27.498
definitely needs
a professional touch.

19:27.725 --> 19:29.074
Oh, more than a touch.

19:29.169 --> 19:32.745
Yeah, we'll have to reframe
all of this.

19:32.839 --> 19:34.505
Mm-hmm. We assumed that.

19:34.674 --> 19:37.416
We were talking about
turning this into a ramp.

19:37.568 --> 19:40.494
-Yeah.
-And then pulling these windows
out and putting in

19:40.663 --> 19:44.331
-double pane.
-Might as well update things
since we at it. (laughs)

19:44.350 --> 19:46.409
Update what?

19:46.427 --> 19:48.260
I like my house.

19:48.354 --> 19:49.503
Mama,

19:49.597 --> 19:52.523
we don't know what's
gonna happen with Daddy.

19:52.692 --> 19:55.193
I mean, he might need to spend
some time at a rehab facility,

19:55.420 --> 19:58.845
but, when he comes home,
we want him to have more space.

19:58.865 --> 20:00.589
You're acting like
he's already dead.

20:00.683 --> 20:01.607
No...

20:01.759 --> 20:02.942
Talking about updating my house.

20:03.094 --> 20:05.703
I'm just trying to give him
quality of life.

20:05.930 --> 20:07.613
You want to sell it.

20:07.690 --> 20:09.040
I'm not surprised.

20:09.267 --> 20:12.601
You'll be glad when
you're rid of us and can go

20:12.603 --> 20:14.620
back to your fancy life

20:14.714 --> 20:15.788
-in California.
-Okay, Beatrice,

20:15.957 --> 20:17.030
that's enough. Stop.

20:17.050 --> 20:18.457
You're not doing this, not now.

20:18.551 --> 20:20.218
-How dare you talk to me
like that.
-BOBBY: I'm sorry.

20:20.445 --> 20:21.961
I know you're in pain,
but so is your daughter,

20:22.055 --> 20:23.203
and she's just trying
to keep things

20:23.223 --> 20:24.613
from crashing down
on both of you.

20:24.632 --> 20:25.872
You don't understand.

20:25.967 --> 20:27.374
So why don't you just
take a second

20:27.393 --> 20:29.310
and cool off.

20:36.218 --> 20:38.644
Guess I'll go to my room,

20:38.796 --> 20:40.738
like a child.

20:46.246 --> 20:47.245
Sorry about that.

20:47.396 --> 20:49.580
You should hear
me and Pops go at it.

20:49.732 --> 20:51.898
They get set in their ways,
turn back into little kids.

20:51.993 --> 20:53.476
We end up parenting our parents.

20:53.494 --> 20:54.585
(laughs)

20:54.812 --> 20:57.813
That is a lot of truth
coming from you, Junior.

20:57.982 --> 20:59.757
Live and learn, Athena.

20:59.984 --> 21:02.760
Live and learn. (laughs)

21:03.838 --> 21:06.097
Mm. Okay.

21:09.660 --> 21:11.844
<i> FRANKIE:</i>
<i> Welcome to the Happiness</i>
<i> Symposium.</i>

21:11.996 --> 21:14.105
I'm Frankie.
Please find your name.

21:14.256 --> 21:16.941
And, uh, here's an itinerary
for day one.

21:17.092 --> 21:19.835
-Sweet. Thank you.
There you go.
-Ronald.

21:19.928 --> 21:22.688
You guys usually travel
in a pack?

21:22.840 --> 21:24.448
Or are you in a band?

21:24.600 --> 21:26.933
(all chuckle)

21:26.953 --> 21:29.695
Uh, we were in a band.

21:29.789 --> 21:32.623
That's where we met.
Sixth grade.

21:32.850 --> 21:34.107
Uh, trombone...

21:34.127 --> 21:36.460
-Uh, trumpet.
-Baritone sax.

21:36.687 --> 21:38.187
-Band buddies.
-Yeah.

21:38.205 --> 21:40.131
All you guys are missing
is a drumline.

21:40.358 --> 21:42.057
We left those at home.

21:42.059 --> 21:43.968
Our wives.
They keep us on the beat.

21:44.119 --> 21:45.303
-Right.
-(laughing)

21:45.530 --> 21:46.862
<i> WOMAN (over comm):</i>
<i> Frankie? Frankie Hannah.</i>

21:46.955 --> 21:48.121
Go for Frankie.

21:48.290 --> 21:49.865
<i> We need more chairs</i>
<i> in the Desert Ballroom.</i>

21:49.958 --> 21:52.201
Copy that.
I'm on my way.

21:52.294 --> 21:55.462
Gentlemen, enjoy your day.

21:55.556 --> 21:56.797
Be happy.

21:56.816 --> 21:58.149
Thanks.

21:58.334 --> 22:00.376
(indistinct chatter)

22:00.469 --> 22:03.321
Here's one about the seven
keys to happiness.

22:03.548 --> 22:04.730
You want to start
with that one?

22:04.882 --> 22:06.215
Sounds good to me.

22:06.233 --> 22:07.566
<i> WOMAN (over P.A.):</i>
<i> Welcome to the WestPlex</i>

22:07.718 --> 22:08.826
<i> Convention Center.</i>

22:08.995 --> 22:10.903
<i> The International</i>
<i> Happiness Symposium</i>

22:10.997 --> 22:13.313
<i> is officially open.</i>

22:13.391 --> 22:15.558
<i> Please, come find</i>
<i> your key to happiness...</i>

22:15.651 --> 22:18.169
"Sponsored by Felicidades
Spirits and Liquor."

22:18.245 --> 22:20.153
Yeah, well, maybe they'll
hand out free drinks.

22:20.231 --> 22:22.565
(laughs) I think they're
sponsoring the whole convention.

22:22.658 --> 22:24.583
I swear to God,
if the key to happiness

22:24.735 --> 22:25.843
is to drink more, I'm out.

22:25.994 --> 22:28.161
God, would you stop?

22:28.181 --> 22:29.738
You have done nothing
but whine

22:29.757 --> 22:31.240
since we landed at LAX.

22:31.258 --> 22:33.166
Come on, a bunch of quacks
gonna teach us

22:33.260 --> 22:35.001
the secret to happiness?

22:35.096 --> 22:36.854
This is one of the dumbest ideas
you ever had.

22:37.005 --> 22:38.581
-Then why did you come?
-(cracking overhead)

22:38.599 --> 22:42.068
-Because he made me.
-You gonna jump in here?

22:45.365 --> 22:47.681
Look out!

22:47.700 --> 22:48.991
(panicked shouting)

22:58.211 --> 23:00.102
Stay where you are.
Help is on the way.

23:00.121 --> 23:03.297
-(sirens wailing)
-(horns honking)

23:19.732 --> 23:21.565
(electricity crackling)

23:21.717 --> 23:23.809
Buck, Chim, you're with him.

23:23.961 --> 23:27.554
Eddie, Julie,
you get these two.

23:27.648 --> 23:29.815
(victims coughing)

23:29.967 --> 23:32.993
Let's get these people
to the treatment area.

23:36.657 --> 23:38.140
(pained groaning)

23:38.233 --> 23:41.067
Ronny, Angelo, I'm Eddie,
this is Julie.

23:41.087 --> 23:44.163
Nice when the bodies are
already tagged, eh, Julie?

23:44.315 --> 23:47.240
Oh, would you shut your trap,
Ange, for once?

23:47.334 --> 23:48.651
Can you both feel your legs?

23:48.669 --> 23:51.153
-More than I'd like.
-Where the hell is Lev?

23:51.172 --> 23:53.155
Is he okay? Lev!

23:53.174 --> 23:55.841
-Kind of in the middle
of something.
-(Angelo groans)

23:55.993 --> 23:57.918
I guess under
the middle of something.

23:57.937 --> 24:01.513
Vitals holding. Let's run
two lines on him, wide open.

24:01.666 --> 24:03.849
(device beeping)

24:04.001 --> 24:05.109
I can't feel anything.

24:05.260 --> 24:07.111
-Is that bad?
-Not necessarily.

24:07.262 --> 24:09.521
Could be some swelling
that's causing the numbness.

24:09.674 --> 24:11.282
Let me take a look.

24:15.029 --> 24:17.455
Uh, hey, so you guys were
attending

24:17.606 --> 24:18.622
the convention together?

24:18.849 --> 24:20.516
Post-retirement boys' trip.

24:20.685 --> 24:23.276
And here I thought everyone just
took up golf when they retired.

24:23.296 --> 24:26.855
-Oh, do not say it.
-I told you so.

24:26.874 --> 24:28.281
Oh, God, he says it.

24:28.301 --> 24:29.967
Seems like you guys have
known each other for a while.

24:30.118 --> 24:32.878
-Ever since sixth grade.
-That's nice.

24:33.030 --> 24:34.454
That you guys have
stayed close this long.

24:34.507 --> 24:36.031
I'd like to be less close
right now,

24:36.050 --> 24:37.700
if you don't mind.
(grunts)

24:37.793 --> 24:39.885
(groans)
Can you move this thing?

24:40.037 --> 24:44.223
All right.
But it is gonna hurt.

24:44.391 --> 24:46.025
(groaning)

24:49.489 --> 24:51.739
All right, ready?

24:52.733 --> 24:54.399
On three.

24:54.494 --> 24:57.244
One, two, three.

24:58.055 --> 25:00.080
(Angelo cries out)

25:02.168 --> 25:05.652
Put it back!
(crying out)

25:05.746 --> 25:08.088
-What happened?
-(Angelo groans)

25:09.083 --> 25:11.675
Your fibula's punctured
his thigh.

25:11.827 --> 25:13.235
Hit a major artery.

25:13.328 --> 25:16.421
Are we gonna be okay?

25:16.590 --> 25:19.683
Yeah. They're in great hands,
and you're next.

25:19.835 --> 25:21.760
Okay. Those two...

25:21.854 --> 25:25.356
will kill each other
without me.

25:25.583 --> 25:26.690
Uh, Lev, hey, hey.

25:26.842 --> 25:28.692
You, uh, you never told me why.

25:28.844 --> 25:30.176
Why a happiness convention, huh?

25:30.196 --> 25:32.755
Trying to figure out
some stuff.

25:32.773 --> 25:35.682
Thought maybe we'd find
an answer here.

25:35.701 --> 25:37.609
You-you guys weren't happy?

25:37.762 --> 25:38.852
You live your whole life,

25:38.946 --> 25:41.855
doing everything
you're supposed to.

25:41.949 --> 25:43.932
Marriage, kids.

25:43.951 --> 25:47.770
Big house, nice cars.

25:47.863 --> 25:50.105
Weekends at the shore.

25:50.198 --> 25:53.108
Hey, that, uh, doesn't sound
too bad, right?

25:53.201 --> 25:53.942
It wasn't.

25:54.036 --> 25:57.780
It's just this 40-year blur.

25:57.798 --> 26:01.450
Work and family.

26:01.468 --> 26:03.710
Never enough time.

26:03.729 --> 26:06.397
Until one day work stops,

26:06.624 --> 26:10.050
and everything finally
comes into focus.

26:10.069 --> 26:13.720
You're not sure what
you're looking at.

26:13.739 --> 26:16.648
What was the point of...

26:16.742 --> 26:19.368
any of it?

26:22.139 --> 26:24.139
I'm here, sir.
Are you able to speak up?

26:24.141 --> 26:26.250
-What's your name?
<i> -Frankie. I'm trapped.</i>

26:26.477 --> 26:27.918
<i> NOAH: Do you know</i>
<i> your address, Frankie?</i>

26:28.070 --> 26:30.479
I'm at the WestPlex
Convention Center.

26:30.497 --> 26:32.314
We've got a team
on scene, Frankie.

26:32.407 --> 26:33.924
<i> I think I'm too buried.</i>

26:34.076 --> 26:35.909
I was up top moving some chairs

26:36.003 --> 26:37.377
when it all came
crashing down.

26:37.488 --> 26:40.322
Captain 118, we've got
another victim on scene.

26:40.341 --> 26:42.841
<i> His name is Frankie.</i>
<i> Says he's completely buried.</i>

26:42.993 --> 26:45.060
(indistinct chatter)

26:46.664 --> 26:48.105
Dispatch, need help
finding a location.

26:48.256 --> 26:51.358
He says he was moving some
chairs from the ballroom.

26:59.526 --> 27:00.934
(grunts)

27:01.028 --> 27:04.179
Frankie!
Where are you hurt?

27:04.198 --> 27:06.123
-Hard to breathe.
-Hang in there, Frankie.

27:06.274 --> 27:08.033
-(whimpers)
-We got him!
-Yeah!

27:08.127 --> 27:11.045
-We're coming to get you.
-(sobs)

27:11.797 --> 27:13.038
No distal pulse on Angelo.

27:13.190 --> 27:15.040
Normally we travel you
with a foreign object,

27:15.134 --> 27:17.968
-but in this case,
the object is your friend.
-So what do we do?

27:18.120 --> 27:21.213
Pull you apart very carefully.

27:21.307 --> 27:24.141
Dispatch, the victim's showing
signs of a punctured lung.

27:24.368 --> 27:27.478
We've already got two
complicated rescues in progress.

27:27.705 --> 27:28.795
133 is already en route.

27:28.814 --> 27:31.315
The 133 will be there
in 12 minutes.

27:33.544 --> 27:34.985
I just, I don't have
enough hands

27:35.212 --> 27:36.561
to get them both out
right now,

27:36.730 --> 27:38.155
and I need the hydraulic jack
for the kid.

27:38.306 --> 27:41.307
Most likely, Lev has already
bled out internally,

27:41.327 --> 27:42.551
and that slab of concrete's

27:42.644 --> 27:44.144
acting as a clamp,
keeping him alive.

27:44.163 --> 27:46.664
We lift it, most likely
he dies anyway.

27:46.891 --> 27:49.208
Kid's got a better shot.

27:56.825 --> 27:59.918
-Hey, Lev...
-Hey.

28:00.012 --> 28:02.137
You ready to get this thing
off of me?

28:04.016 --> 28:05.999
There's a kid buried
over there.

28:06.018 --> 28:09.228
I think he's got
a punctured lung.

28:10.931 --> 28:12.338
I-I need to get him
out of there.

28:12.433 --> 28:15.984
And you don't have
enough guys.

28:17.938 --> 28:20.847
You get that kid out.

28:20.941 --> 28:22.774
I ain't going nowhere.

28:22.868 --> 28:24.535
Go help the kid.

28:24.686 --> 28:26.245
Buck.

28:28.949 --> 28:31.283
Help me with this.

28:31.435 --> 28:33.043
(grunts)

28:34.362 --> 28:36.438
-(hydraulic jack whining)
-Are you guys clear?

28:36.457 --> 28:38.790
I always thought it was Lev
that kept us together.

28:38.867 --> 28:41.944
(pained groaning)

28:42.037 --> 28:43.946
(groaning continues)

28:44.039 --> 28:46.039
All right, pull him out.

28:46.133 --> 28:47.632
BUCK:
All right, get him
on the backboard.

28:47.727 --> 28:49.952
One, two, three.

28:50.120 --> 28:52.730
(Angelo, Ronny crying out)

29:01.298 --> 29:03.148
-CHIMNEY: Clear?
-EDDIE: Ready, yeah.

29:03.242 --> 29:04.658
Up.

29:07.154 --> 29:09.654
Three, two, up.

29:09.749 --> 29:11.656
BUCK:
We got him. We got him.

29:11.809 --> 29:13.976
-They saved the kid?
-Yeah.

29:14.069 --> 29:16.812
And you're next.
You're next, Lev.

29:16.830 --> 29:19.906
It's okay.

29:20.000 --> 29:23.051
I got what I came for.

29:25.656 --> 29:28.432
I think I get it now.

29:28.583 --> 29:30.893
(monitor flatlines)

29:31.829 --> 29:33.270
Get him out.
Get him out now!

29:34.181 --> 29:36.681
("Don't Worry, Be Happy"
playing)

29:36.834 --> 29:39.276
(grunting)

29:39.503 --> 29:42.687
♪<i> Here's a little song</i>
<i> I wrote...</i> ♪

29:42.782 --> 29:46.658
-HEN: Chim, we need that jack.
-I'm on it.

29:47.528 --> 29:50.846
♪<i> Don't worry</i> ♪

29:50.864 --> 29:52.772
Okay, moving it.

29:52.792 --> 29:54.850
♪<i> Be happy</i> ♪

29:54.868 --> 29:56.418
Come on, come on.

29:58.080 --> 30:01.781
♪<i> In every life</i>
<i> there comes some trouble</i> ♪

30:01.801 --> 30:03.358
Hey, Lev! Come on!

30:03.377 --> 30:07.546
♪<i> But when you worry,</i>
<i> you make it double</i> ♪

30:07.698 --> 30:09.714
♪<i> Don't worry</i> ♪

30:09.867 --> 30:12.534
(grunting)

30:12.553 --> 30:13.535
♪<i> Be happy...</i> ♪

30:13.537 --> 30:15.628
(shouting)

30:15.648 --> 30:16.980
(Hen grunts)

30:17.132 --> 30:20.542
Starting compressions!
(grunting)

30:20.561 --> 30:23.320
<i> (singer vocalizing)</i>

30:28.476 --> 30:29.718
Time of death...

30:29.736 --> 30:31.662
(gasping)

30:31.889 --> 30:34.239
...16:43.

30:34.333 --> 30:37.125
(panting)

30:38.337 --> 30:42.247
♪<i> So here's this little song</i>
<i> I wrote</i> ♪

30:42.399 --> 30:46.659
♪<i> Hope you learned it</i>
<i> note for note</i> ♪

30:46.737 --> 30:49.096
♪<i> Don't worry</i> ♪

30:50.850 --> 30:54.351
♪<i> Be happy.</i> ♪

31:03.011 --> 31:05.511
(thunder rumbling)

31:05.606 --> 31:08.323
(rain falling)

31:11.945 --> 31:13.612
You want some company?

31:13.764 --> 31:16.039
Mm. Sure.

31:18.936 --> 31:22.713
There's an old orange grove
out there.

31:22.789 --> 31:24.940
Out past the woods.

31:24.958 --> 31:27.200
Where the bonfires happened

31:27.294 --> 31:30.295
when we all hung out
in high school.

31:30.447 --> 31:33.390
When I was a little girl,

31:33.617 --> 31:34.799
Daddy and I would
go out there

31:34.894 --> 31:36.894
every Saturday morning,

31:37.045 --> 31:40.122
grab oranges and tangerines

31:40.140 --> 31:41.973
that had fallen from the trees.

31:42.067 --> 31:45.218
Bring 'em home,
make fresh juice,

31:45.312 --> 31:50.815
pour it over ice and sit,
right here. (chuckles)

31:50.910 --> 31:54.302
I would sit on his lap.

31:54.396 --> 31:57.230
He would tell me stories
about the family,

31:57.399 --> 32:01.609
about all the great things
that the Carters had done.

32:01.662 --> 32:04.237
Daddy was an attorney,

32:04.256 --> 32:08.074
but his daddy
had been one, too.

32:08.093 --> 32:11.836
First Negro lawyer
to pass the Florida bar.

32:11.931 --> 32:15.248
Even graduated from A&M
just like him.

32:15.267 --> 32:17.434
And that's what made you
want to be a lawyer.

32:17.585 --> 32:20.020
Oh, it did.

32:20.922 --> 32:22.998
And when I left for California,

32:23.091 --> 32:25.167
oh, he couldn't have
been prouder.

32:25.185 --> 32:30.689
Told me to spread my wings,
do great things.

32:30.841 --> 32:32.507
And what did Beatrice say?

32:32.526 --> 32:35.844
"Do not drink that juice,
it has not been pasteurized."

32:35.862 --> 32:37.746
(Bobby chuckles)

32:38.791 --> 32:41.458
Daddy was always the comfort.

32:41.609 --> 32:44.294
Mama was the reality.

32:45.372 --> 32:48.781
I'm not sure I'm ready
to lose the comfort.

32:48.801 --> 32:50.968
You haven't lost him yet.

32:52.529 --> 32:57.391
You know the worst part of
having to parent your parents?

32:58.811 --> 33:00.644
It's knowing that you're
that much closer

33:00.871 --> 33:03.105
to losing them.

33:14.067 --> 33:16.159
Hey, uh, we're gonna grab
some breakfast.

33:16.311 --> 33:18.978
A little grub might
hit the spot.

33:18.998 --> 33:22.724
Uh, not for me.
Not today.

33:22.743 --> 33:24.743
Fair enough.

33:24.895 --> 33:27.078
I gotta pass.

33:27.172 --> 33:29.397
Copy that. Well-we'll be
at the diner on Alvarado

33:29.416 --> 33:31.717
if you guys want to join us.

33:44.339 --> 33:48.984
Hey, um, what...
What do you think he meant?

33:50.029 --> 33:52.270
You know, he said,
"I get it now."

33:52.422 --> 33:55.090
And his eyes got all bright,
and he looked up to the sky

33:55.108 --> 33:57.108
like he'd just found happiness.

33:57.261 --> 33:58.351
I was there, Buck.

33:58.370 --> 33:59.685
It was like he solved this...

33:59.780 --> 34:01.538
this great mystery,

34:01.689 --> 34:03.749
and then he died
before he could share it.

34:07.287 --> 34:12.532
Hey, losing someone
out there is never easy.

34:12.551 --> 34:15.443
Uh-huh. Yeah.

34:15.462 --> 34:16.386
To a design flaw.

34:16.613 --> 34:20.131
I, uh, saw it
on the news last night.

34:20.208 --> 34:22.801
The hotel put in that walkway
a couple years ago

34:22.953 --> 34:26.212
and tried to sue the contractor
after they found some cracks

34:26.306 --> 34:27.305
but the repairs just...

34:27.399 --> 34:29.291
Fell through the same cracks.

34:29.309 --> 34:31.476
It was bound to come
crashing down.

34:31.628 --> 34:35.888
But not before Nathan Levinson
learned the secret, right?

34:35.908 --> 34:39.634
Maybe that's what
we should focus on.

34:39.727 --> 34:42.304
-He found it before he died.
-What, so he,

34:42.472 --> 34:44.581
he spent his whole life
trying to figure it out,

34:44.732 --> 34:48.043
and then he finally gets
the answer right at the end?

34:49.146 --> 34:52.238
What, uh, what do you
think it is?

34:52.257 --> 34:54.407
The secret to happiness.

34:54.426 --> 34:56.668
(scoffs)

34:56.762 --> 34:58.637
I mean, Hen...

35:00.157 --> 35:02.599
...you-you always
have the answers.

35:02.750 --> 35:04.326
(chuckles softly)

35:04.344 --> 35:07.229
Some answers you gotta
find on your own, Buck.

35:08.923 --> 35:12.025
(phone ringing, vibrating)

35:15.339 --> 35:17.114
Hello?

35:17.265 --> 35:22.035
Hi, Dr. Simmons.
This is a surprise.

35:39.379 --> 35:41.379
Good morning.

35:41.456 --> 35:43.365
Hey.

35:44.459 --> 35:47.886
You know, when I said
you had to let something go,

35:48.038 --> 35:51.389
I didn't think it was
gonna be your son.

35:51.483 --> 35:54.133
Oh, damn.

35:54.153 --> 35:57.654
(sighs)
His robotics meet.

35:57.881 --> 35:59.047
-Is Denny here?
-He called me

35:59.065 --> 36:00.806
when he couldn't reach you.

36:00.826 --> 36:03.401
Did he make it in time?

36:03.495 --> 36:06.646
Yes.

36:06.740 --> 36:08.481
Okay, that's good.

36:08.500 --> 36:10.375
That's good...

36:11.728 --> 36:12.894
Are you all right?

36:12.913 --> 36:15.505
-(groans)
-Hen.

36:20.737 --> 36:23.087
I failed. I failed.

36:23.240 --> 36:24.830
Failed at what?

36:24.925 --> 36:27.575
(crying):
Everything.

36:27.744 --> 36:29.093
Everything. I failed...

36:29.246 --> 36:31.262
-Oh, honey.
-...at everything.

36:31.356 --> 36:34.524
Okay. Okay, baby, it's okay.

36:34.751 --> 36:36.418
(Hen sobbing)

36:36.586 --> 36:38.195
Hey.

36:45.612 --> 36:47.871
(Beatrice grunting)

36:48.098 --> 36:50.707
Beatrice. You need some help?

36:50.934 --> 36:53.293
I don't think I can reach it.

36:58.533 --> 37:00.366
There you go.

37:00.460 --> 37:02.368
Thank you.

37:02.387 --> 37:03.445
You're welcome.

37:03.463 --> 37:08.040
Beatrice...
I want to apologize.

37:08.134 --> 37:12.896
Never apologize for standing up
for my baby girl.

37:12.973 --> 37:16.399
Taking care of her
is your job now.

37:16.626 --> 37:19.152
Do it well.

37:20.130 --> 37:22.155
Yes, ma'am.

37:38.665 --> 37:41.299
-Hey.
-Mm.

37:42.652 --> 37:43.835
What time is it?

37:43.929 --> 37:47.505
It's almost 3:00.
You crashed hard.

37:47.674 --> 37:50.767
(grunts)
In many ways.

37:50.994 --> 37:54.754
(sighs) It's not the end
of the world, Hen.

37:54.773 --> 37:56.848
(sputters, sighs)

37:57.000 --> 37:59.667
Karen, I failed neurology.

37:59.686 --> 38:03.947
Dr. Simmons thinks that I should
repeat my second year.

38:04.098 --> 38:07.450
I-I can't do this
for another year.

38:07.602 --> 38:10.845
These past few weeks
almost killed me.

38:10.938 --> 38:14.106
(chuckles)
I-I know they were hard

38:14.126 --> 38:19.170
but let's maybe ease up
on the hyperbole.

38:24.469 --> 38:28.221
Wait. What am I missing?

38:31.051 --> 38:35.812
The other night.
After my neurology exam.

38:36.873 --> 38:39.465
I fell asleep
behind the wheel.

38:39.559 --> 38:43.486
♪ ♪

38:43.713 --> 38:45.447
(scoffs)

38:46.733 --> 38:50.902
You have to choose, Hen.

38:50.996 --> 38:53.237
Doctor or paramedic.

38:53.390 --> 38:55.498
You can't be both anymore.

38:55.650 --> 38:59.711
Because this family
needs you too much.

39:07.829 --> 39:10.755
"Dear Beatrice,

39:10.907 --> 39:12.515
"I miss you.

39:12.708 --> 39:15.076
"I miss home.

39:15.169 --> 39:17.854
"I love you.

39:18.081 --> 39:20.506
And I want to come home
to Florida."

39:20.525 --> 39:22.600
Hey, Mama.

39:22.752 --> 39:25.753
I came to give you a break.

39:25.755 --> 39:27.179
I'm doing fine.

39:27.199 --> 39:29.607
Well, why don't you
take a walk?

39:29.759 --> 39:32.927
Stretch your legs a bit.
I'll watch over him.

39:33.096 --> 39:36.331
Why don't you come
and sit with me a bit?

39:46.033 --> 39:49.293
-These are all from Daddy?
-Mm-hmm.

39:50.055 --> 39:53.873
He used to write me
a letter every day.

39:53.892 --> 39:55.875
When we were courting.

39:55.894 --> 39:59.637
-(laughs softly)
-When he was in Vietnam.

39:59.789 --> 40:04.308
Not one day in 57 years

40:04.461 --> 40:09.147
that we didn't have
some kind of communication.

40:09.299 --> 40:11.991
Some kind of connection.

40:13.470 --> 40:15.245
Until now.

40:18.065 --> 40:23.420
(sighs) I know what
the doctors are scared about,

40:23.571 --> 40:26.089
what you're afraid of.

40:26.240 --> 40:32.745
If he wakes up, will he be able
to walk or feed himself?

40:32.764 --> 40:35.915
Or will he even be himself?

40:35.934 --> 40:41.679
I'm not sure I care about
any of that...

40:41.831 --> 40:45.483
(crying):
a-as long as...

40:46.352 --> 40:49.929
You can hear his voice again.

40:50.023 --> 40:54.451
Even just one more time.

40:54.527 --> 40:57.245
(crying)

41:03.687 --> 41:06.612
♪ ♪

41:06.706 --> 41:08.447
(sighs)

41:08.467 --> 41:11.426
(sirens wailing)

41:15.699 --> 41:17.474
(siren whoops)

41:17.701 --> 41:19.142
(camera clicking)

41:19.811 --> 41:21.728
(door chiming)

41:23.297 --> 41:26.040
My parents live here.
And I'm a cop.

41:26.133 --> 41:27.525
(door opens)

41:28.712 --> 41:30.487
Athena!

41:32.398 --> 41:34.215
Athena, I've been
trying to call you.

41:34.234 --> 41:36.567
I-I forgot my charger.
The phone died two hours ago.

41:36.720 --> 41:39.662
What is going on?
Why are the police here?

41:39.889 --> 41:41.072
I was helping Junior out.

41:41.224 --> 41:43.482
We were digging
up the foundation...

41:43.502 --> 41:44.909
And what?

41:45.061 --> 41:47.745
Athena, we found a body.

41:47.897 --> 41:50.064
(distorted):
Small, maybe a child.

41:50.083 --> 41:52.491
Not sure how long
they've been down there.

41:52.585 --> 41:54.159
(camera clicking loudly)

41:54.179 --> 41:56.495
(echoing): Sir, can you
come here for a minute?

41:56.548 --> 41:58.848
I just want to
show you something.

41:59.000 --> 42:00.499
<i> ATHENA:</i>
<i> Did I ever tell you about</i>

42:00.519 --> 42:03.502
<i> when I decided to become</i>
<i> an officer of the law?</i>

42:03.522 --> 42:05.980
I was nine years old.

42:06.766 --> 42:09.250
Middle of the night,

42:09.269 --> 42:12.011
<i> I wake up and I see</i>
<i> my father getting dressed.</i>

42:12.030 --> 42:14.605
<i> Grabbing a flashlight.</i>

42:14.758 --> 42:17.367
<i> His gun.</i>

42:17.594 --> 42:19.110
<i>I look out the window and I see</i>

42:19.262 --> 42:22.372
<i> the whole neighborhood</i>
<i> out there.</i>

42:22.523 --> 42:27.602
<i> A little girl, she was</i>
<i> a-a grade behind me at school,</i>

42:27.695 --> 42:29.528
<i> had gone missing.</i>

42:30.290 --> 42:34.551
<i> Someone had just snatched her</i>
<i> right out of her bed.</i>

42:34.778 --> 42:38.871
<i> HEN: Wow, that's a nightmare.</i>
<i> Did they find her?</i>

42:40.116 --> 42:43.542
<i> ATHENA: They found a barrette,</i>
<i> out of her hair.</i>

42:43.562 --> 42:45.453
<i> Out in the woods.</i>

42:45.471 --> 42:47.471
<i> But that was it.</i>

42:47.624 --> 42:49.381
<i> She was just gone.</i>

42:49.401 --> 42:51.976
<i> I promised myself</i>
<i> that when I was old enough</i>

42:52.128 --> 42:53.644
<i> I was gonna become</i>
<i> a policewoman</i>

42:53.738 --> 42:57.632
<i> and find that little girl...</i>

42:57.650 --> 43:00.118
Tanya Kingston.

